label: Basel, Universitätsbibliothek, A I 14

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This meticulously executed manuscript contains the first part of Thomas Aquinas’s Summa theologiae, one of the Scholastic’s main works; it is from the library of Johannes de Lapide, Carthusian monk in Basel. The quires consist of paper and parchment in regular alteration; the proem begins with an ornamental page decorated with gold with a Q-initial on gold leaf, scroll ornamentation with flowers and berries in the margins, and a decorated intercolumnium.

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Restorer: Bitz, Wilhelm; Librarian: Carpentarii, Georgius; Annotator: Heynlin, Johannes; Former possessor: Heynlin, Johannes; Annotator: Pfister, Conrad; Author: Thomas, de Aquino
